title: Volleyball: Lady Red Elephants claim first round state playoff win
text:
By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles Class AAAA volleyball: North Hall knocks off Grady in opening round Class AAA volleyball: East Hall sweeps Glenn Hills; Jefferson up next in 2nd round Class AAA volleyball: Jefferson sweeps N. Clayton, advances to 2nd round Volleyball: Area squads begin their playoff quests this week 
GAINESVILLE — The Gainesville volleyball team cruised through the first round of the state volleyball playoffs on Thursday, defeating Alexander, 3-0 (25-16, 25-22, 25-14). 
The Lady Red Elephants (36-11) were ked by Sydney King led with 2 assists, 3 aces, and 17 digs. Caroline Mercer added 4 digs. Tangi Miller pitched in 4 kills and 1 dig. Bessie Winston had 5 kills, 1 dig, and 1 block. Sally Callahan added 1 dig. Tanai Watson had 9 kills, 2 aces, and 5 digs. Cori Griffith added 2 kills and 1 dig. Abby Alexander had 2 kills and 3 blocks. Anna Wylie had 2 kills and 2 blocks. Savannah Roys had 3 kills, 23 assists, and 14 digs. 
Gainesville moves on to the second roundof the Class postseason, where it will host Ola (from McDonough) on Tuesday. Associated Tags : High school volleyball, Gainesville volleyball © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
